              "name": "note1",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "1. Keep labels visible for forms and reviews. Once text grows, placeholder-only meaning becomes too fragile.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "ynQrE",
              "name": "note2",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "2. Counters should reassure, not dominate. Place them in the lower edge with secondary contrast.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "DRces",
              "name": "note3",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "3. Use filled only when the surrounding UI already has enough borders. Otherwise outline stays clearer over time.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Z90gh",
              "name": "note4",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "4. If the field becomes the main task, let it grow or move the flow to a dedicated editor instead of trapping it in a tiny box.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
