          "gap": 14,
          "padding": 28,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "jgoVq",
              "name": "notesTitle",
              "fill": "$text-primary",
              "content": "System Notes",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 24,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "wnsro",
              "name": "notesDesc",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Choice controls should make selection logic obvious before the user reads helper copy.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "1ZNiy",
              "name": "note1",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "1. Use checkbox for independent toggles or grouped multi-select. Use radio when exactly one option must win.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "HvrcE",
              "name": "note2",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "2. Keep labels close and clickable. The control should not drift away from the meaning it changes.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "W4FeT",
              "name": "note3",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "3. Indeterminate means partial selection, not uncertainty. Only use it when a parent-child selection model actually exists.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "fXdnk",
              "name": "note4",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "4. Radio groups should stay short. If choices become numerous or descriptive, move to select or segmented patterns instead.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
