          },
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 14,
          "padding": 28,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "WPqAN",
              "name": "notesTitle",
              "fill": "$text-primary",
              "content": "System Notes",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 24,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "3xA1H",
              "name": "notesDesc",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Tabs should move users across related content, not force them to discover unrelated modes.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "KqEaH",
              "name": "note1",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "1. Use tabs for sibling sections that share context. If each tab changes the entire task model, consider navigation instead.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "KaV79",
              "name": "note2",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "2. Keep labels short and comparable. Users should scan the set quickly without wrapping or truncation pressure.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "7MsZf",
              "name": "note3",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "3. Only the current tab should get the strongest emphasis. Avoid making every tab look interactive at the same intensity.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "lJrUF",
              "name": "note4",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "4. If the user needs to compare all options side by side as a direct choice, segmented control may be a better fit.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
